paste <(cat <<'EOF'

VIMDIFF CHEATSHEET
==================

LAUNCH
------
vimdiff file1 file2  Diff two files
:diffsplit file2     Diff file2 from inside Vim

NAVIGATION
----------
]c                   Next change
[c                   Previous change

COPY CHANGES BETWEEN WINDOWS
----------------------------
do                   Obtain change from other window
dp                   Put change into other window

EOF
) <(cat <<'EOF'

GENERAL CONCEPTS
----------------
You can edit the files using 
normal vim edit commands

FOLDING (COLLAPSED BLOCKS)
--------------------------
zo          Open fold under cursor
zO          Open fold recursively
za          Alternate fold/unfold
zR          Reveal all folds
zM          Mash down all folds

WINDOW MOVEMENT
---------------
Ctrl-w h    Move to left window
Ctrl-w l    Move to right window
Ctrl-w k    Move to upper window
Ctrl-w j    Move to lower window

EOF
) | awk -F'\t' '{ printf "%-55s  %s\n", $1, $2 }'
